This module deals with all the manipulation to be done to the Products table

1. add_product(pysql, product_id, name, description, unit_price, unit_type, current_discount = None) :

    - Adds new product to global product inventory

    pysql : PySql object for current database

    product_id : id of product (string) (Expected syntax : ABC-01)

    name : Name of the product to be added which will be displayed to the user (string)

    description : Describe the product in less than 64 characters (string)

    unit_price : Price per unit of the product (float)

    unit_type : "kg" or "pcs" (string)

    current_discount(optional) : percentage discount to be offered on the final price of the product(float)

2. update_product_discount(pysql, product_id, discount) : 

    - update the current discount field of product

    pysql : PySql object of current database

    product_id : id of target product

    discount : updated value of current discount(float)

3. update_product_price(pysql, product_id, price) : 

    - update the unit price field of product

    pysql : PySql object of current database

    product_id : id of target product

    price : updated value of the unit price of the product(float)

4. is_product_id_used(pysql, product_id) : 

    - checks if the given product_id is already been used by another product. Returns a 
      boolean. 0 means not used. 1 means used.

    pysql : PySql object of current database

    product_id : the id to be cross-checked with local database
